document.discussion_title: Team 1 through to mixed decider | Central Western Daily
document.topic_text: 12 Aug 2016, 10:25 a.m. A wrap-up from the last week in squash. GREAT GAME: Rhona Baker defeated Narelle Fowler on Wednesday. Photo:CONTRIBUTED THE pressure was telling in the Wednesday night mixed squash competition. Team 5 Tracey lost their star player Belinda Thurtell to injury minutes before starting the major semi. Team 1 Burke took full advantage with Scott Burke and George Eleftheriou winning well. Yvonne Tracey beat Robyn Chapman in five while Kim Knight was clinical winning in three. Wednesday’s star was Scott Baker, who beat Rod Bevan in four, earning a grand final place. Team 4 Vansoest snuck past Team 6 Kidson in the minor semi with Rhona Baker winning in three and Matt Vansoest upsetting Tom Boog. Chris Elkington run down in five by Nathan Garton and Graham Kidson downed Robert Ryan in five. Charles D’Aquino and Luke Kidson battled to remain in contention, with Charlie prevailing in four, leaving Luke despondent. The preliminary final is Monday at 8pm. RESULTS: Team 1 (6 pts) def Team 5 (1 pt): George Eleftheriou def Mark Goes 3-0 Scott Baker def Rod Bevan 3-1 Scott Burke def Tom Secheny 3-1 Kim Knight def Tony Elliot 3-0 Yvonne Tracey def Robyn Chapman 3-2 MINOR SEMI-FINAL: Team 4 (5 pts) def Team 6 (2 pts): Charles Daquino def Luke Kidson 3-1 Nathan Garton def Chris Elkington 3-2 Graham Kidson def Robert Ryan 3-2 Matt Vansoest def Tom Boog 3-1 Rhona Baker def Narelle Fowler 3-0 Latest News
